Massachusetts General Laws, Chapter 185C.proposition: This Court has jurisdiction over this matter pursuant to Massachusetts General Laws, Chapter 185C, Section 21, as the action arises from a landlord-tenant relationship within Worcester County.

Massachusetts General Laws, Chapter 186,.proposition: The Defendant's failure to adequately address and remedy the rodent infestation in the rental unit constitutes a breach of the implied warranty of habitability and the covenant of quiet enjoyment, as guaranteed under Massachusetts General Laws, Chapter 186, Section 14.
